definitions.definition: A parrot belonging to any of the five to eight species in the genus Platycercus (originally specifically Platycercus eximius ) which is native to Australia and nearby islands. [from 19th c.]

main_definition: A parrot belonging to any of the five to eight species in the genus Platycercus (originally specifically Platycercus eximius ) which is native to Australia and nearby islands. [from 19th c.]
